Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:02.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aya. What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.89,0:04:05.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.35,0:04:12.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about time to change your Uro-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.52,0:04:14.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:16.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sometimes my letters are torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:21.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I get ones that aren't for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.95,0:04:27.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're still at it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.16,0:04:30.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using our old ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:33.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:40.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to stop worrying about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:42.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man must be rolling over in his grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:47.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan's still around somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:52.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we can't bring her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.98,0:04:59.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,All we can do is hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:14.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aya-chan. This cocoon's empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:17.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is. Weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:21.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where'd the pupa go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.38,0:05:24.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya, Ito. Put that back where you found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.13,0:05:28.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't touch empty cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.68,0:05:30.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:34.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's bad things living in them in place of the pupa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.75,0:05:58.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the old man from the head house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:06:01.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He comes a lot these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:07.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come here, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:10.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito and Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.26,0:06:15.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you two remember the old man in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:19.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old man in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:24.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've met him when you were two years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:31.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is our family tradition to test new\Nchildren when they are born.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:49.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems these two can both see the Uro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:56.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will come for one of them when they're ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.90,0:07:05.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiisama is an Uro-keeper in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.90,0:07:05.36,notes,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fad(150,150)\be1}Jiisama: Old Man
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:10.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We of the Tozawa family have done\Nthis for many generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:14.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it has been long since anyone\Nhas been born capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.20,0:07:19.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of you will have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:24.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your parents can't decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:30.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one is Aya, the younger daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:34.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:39.02,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiisama, I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:41.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.81,0:07:42.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:43.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:47.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Ito-chan's going, I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:49.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:57.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be hard on you two,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:08:02.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it would be best for your daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.50,0:08:07.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiisama will not be here for much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:15.22,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be cruel to have her alone deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:21.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll be better off together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.52,0:08:24.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not as if you'll never see them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave the door a crack open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.56,0:09:04.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll get sucked in if there's an Uro-san here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:12.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful that you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:14.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.11,0:09:20.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've waited for a long time for this day to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:24.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I never thought there'd be two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.79,0:09:29.46,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been living here alone all this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.17,0:09:34.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, ever since the lady from\Nthe past generation died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:40.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've only had the Mushi-shi to talk to,\Nwhen they'd come ever so often.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.81,0:09:44.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their stories were the only things\NI had to look forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:46.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:56.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've written down piles of their stories for you to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:09:58.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.16,0:10:00.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.96,0:10:14.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This cocoon's empty too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:17.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's more than in the mountains at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:21.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you two know what a double cocoon is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.01,0:10:22.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.72,0:10:26.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a big cocoon that two pupa make together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:31.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is. Find me one that is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.90,0:10:35.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I need one for my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.55,0:11:05.89,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, a cocoon is made of one string.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:11.10,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a double cocoon is made by two pupa,\Nso they are made of two strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:17.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I take them apart and make them\Ninto two cocoons again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.90,0:11:23.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "room" gets thin, and so the Uro-san\Ngets confused and comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:27.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya, catch it with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:39.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good, now put that in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.29,0:11:45.30,caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\pos(772,462)}One
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.59,0:11:45.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it is concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:52.81,caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\move(342,418,342,577)\c&H4E5658&}Nest\NTwo
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.32,0:11:52.81,caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\move(820,241,820,400,0,7475)}Nest\NOne
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.31,0:11:52.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Uro-san can only travel between these two cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:11:58.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiisan, mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.40,0:12:01.86,caligraph,,0,0,0,,{\an8\3c&HDFE7E9&\shad0\bord2.5\c&H484F4F&\3a&H00&}Son fallen ill, vomiting day and night, weakning day by day,\Ncannot even lift a spoon. Urgently requesting a Mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.74,0:12:07.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, whose turn was it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.29,0:12:09.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:11.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.04,0:12:15.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's a request for a Mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:18.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's personal mail for a Mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.59,0:12:21.38,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I'll choose this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:26.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mushi-shi are wanderers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:29.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if I put a letter in the first cocoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.14,0:12:35.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,the Uro-san will eventually take it to the second\Ncocoon that the Mushi-shi carries with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:41.36,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they need to be replaced every few years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.61,0:12:47.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uro-san slowly widen the hole from within their cocoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:54.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eventually they pierce into another\Nclosed chamber or into an Uroana.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:54.33,notes,,0,0,0,,{\an8\fad(150,0)\be1}Uroana: the Hollow
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:58.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the letters don't arrive properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.30,0:13:01.71,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uro-san sounds fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:05.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiisama, I want to do the next letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.93,0:13:10.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito, Aya, don't underestimate the Uro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.64,0:13:17.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uro-san are frightening Mushi that\Nopen fissures in existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:22.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of Uro-san in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:25.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They find closed chambers and spawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:29.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never ever close the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.78,0:13:34.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do, don't ever open them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.12,0:13:39.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you open them and there's an Uro-san inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.29,0:13:45.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,you'll get sucked in when it leaves for an Uroana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.97,0:13:51.26,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uro-san can't be outside of closed chambers for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:55.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happens if you get sucked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:14:01.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say you'll be trapped wandering\Ninside the Uroana forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:06.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, just do as I say and you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:11.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've survived for as long as I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.16,0:14:13.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't close.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:16.21,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.13,0:14:26.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:29.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you done doing the laundry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.97,0:14:30.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:33.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jiichan said we can play until sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:34.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.97,0:14:37.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go put this away, one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.35,0:14:39.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:43.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,watch out for the shed door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:45.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.45,0:14:52.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:19.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.02,0:15:21.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.07,0:15:34.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan, are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:36.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't lift it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:44.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.31,0:16:02.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because I turned the cloth over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:06.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I didn't pin the cloth down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:11.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya, it's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.07,0:16:16.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did Ito-chan go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.45,0:16:20.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can I bring her back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:27.00,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing we can do, Aya.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:31.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to bring her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:37.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:43.39,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was always with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:50.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never even thought about what it'd be like without her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.07,0:16:53.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's been five years since then, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:57.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you still don't eat much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:17:00.66,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time you start thinking about yourself a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.71,0:17:06.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we go into the Uroana then?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:10.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go in with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.63,0:17:15.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,See for yourself what it's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.65,0:17:27.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:33.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,When an Uro spawns inside a Koumyakusuji tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.28,0:17:37.32,dialogue,,0,0,0,,it causes a rejection reaction and forms into a gall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.24,0:17:44.37,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on to the chain and follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:08.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the Uroana?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:11.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:14.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll soon be in the great Uroana.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:27.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who put this chain down?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.96,0:18:29.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Mushi-shi from long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:33.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an old pathway that the\NMushi-shi have been using.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:38.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard that some people stayed for\Ntoo long and lost their memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.34,0:18:40.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't use it too much myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.66,0:19:02.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, aren't you coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.75,0:19:20.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that the only hole leading to the\Noutside is at the end of this chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.30,0:19:26.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything else is connected to some closed chamber
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:29.89,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and can't be opened from inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:34.90,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are countless such Uroanas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.61,0:19:42.61,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely that your sister might have even\Npassed through one of these Uroanas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.41,0:19:49.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.66,0:19:53.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aya, please, give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.38,0:20:02.18,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Close that big hole within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.39,0:20:05.05,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before it's too late to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:37.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ito-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.58,0:21:20.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a few years since then that something strange
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.59,0:21:25.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,was said to have happened in\Na village of silkworm farmers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.10,0:21:36.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A child of man, from a cocoon she appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:40.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps ten years of age, she was without speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.07,0:21:44.65,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:48.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone come, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:56.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Home she returned, with the letter\Nin her pocket to guide her.
